The Minister of Higher Education, Science and Innovation, Dr. Blade Nzimande, will release the outcome of the HSRC second part of the public perception survey on the impact of the coronavirus on South Africans. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Higher Education Dr Blade Nzimande will release the outcome of the Human Sciences Research Council (HSRC) second part of the public perception survey on the impact of the coronavirus on South Africans. This follows the first survey conducted from 27-31 March during which the council looked at how South Africans feel about the survey, what they understand, know and how they are reacting to the COVID-19 emergency. WATCH: Ramaphosa addresses nation on COVID-19 economic measures The second wave of the survey which was conducted from 7-14 April, looked specifically at the lockdown as implemented from 27 March to 16 April. South Africa has recorded over 4,000 cases of the virus.